---
import Layout from "../../components/layout/BaseLayout.astro"

const lastUpdated = "May 9, 2026"
---

<Layout
    lang="en"
    title="Privacy Policy - Javier Piedra"
    description="Information on personal data processing at jpiedra.com under GDPR and Spanish data protection law."
>
    <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8 py-32 lg:py-40">
        <header class="mb-16">
            <p
                class="text-xs font-body font-medium tracking-[0.3em] text-accent uppercase mb-6"
            >
                Legal information
            </p>
            <h1
                class="font-heading text-[clamp(2rem,4.5vw,3.5rem)] leading-[1.1] text-text-primary mb-6"
            >
                Privacy Policy
            </h1>
            <p class="text-sm text-text-muted font-body">
                Last updated: {lastUpdated}
            </p>
        </header>

        <div
            class="legal-content flex flex-col gap-10 text-text-primary font-body leading-relaxed"
        >
            <section>
                <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl mb-4">1. Data controller</h2>
                <p>
                    The controller of the personal data collected through this
                    website is:
                </p>
                <ul class="mt-4 space-y-1">
                    <li><strong>Owner:</strong> Javier Piedra</li>
                    <li><strong>Tax ID (NIF):</strong> 70256299Q</li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Address:</strong> 40194 Palazuelos de Eresma (Segovia),
                        Spain
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Email:</strong>
                        <a
                            href="mailto:contacto@jpiedra.com"
                            class="text-accent underline underline-offset-2"
                            >contacto@jpiedra.com</a
                        >
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl mb-4">
                    2. Purpose of processing
                </h2>
                <p>
                    Personal data submitted by the user through the contact form
                    on this website is processed for the following purposes:
                </p>
                <ul class="mt-4 list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
                    <li>
                        To respond to the user's request, query, or information
                        inquiry.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        To maintain the commercial communication necessary to
                        evaluate a potential professional relationship.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        To comply with applicable legal obligations (tax,
                        accounting, or otherwise).
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <p class="mt-4">
                    No profiling or automated decision-making is carried out on
                    the data provided.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl mb-4">3. Data collected</h2>
                <p>The following data is collected through the contact form:</p>
                <ul class="mt-4 list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
                    <li>Name.</li>
                    <li>Email address.</li>
                    <li>Website (optional).</li>
                    <li>
                        Message and any additional information the user
                        voluntarily includes in it.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Date and time of acceptance of this privacy policy, as
                        proof of consent.
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <p class="mt-4">
                    The user is responsible for the accuracy of the data
                    provided and undertakes not to provide third-party
                    information without their express consent.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl mb-4">
                    4. Legal basis for processing
                </h2>
                <p>The legal basis for processing the data is:</p>
                <ul class="mt-4 list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
                    <li>
                        <strong>The user's consent,</strong> expressly given by ticking
                        the acceptance box for this policy before submitting the form
                        (Article 6.1.a GDPR).
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Compliance with legal obligations</strong> applicable
                        to the controller, in particular regarding tax and accounting
                        matters (Article 6.1.c GDPR).
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl mb-4">5. Retention period</h2>
                <p>
                    Personal data will be retained for as long as necessary to
                    fulfill the purpose for which it was collected:
                </p>
                <ul class="mt-4 list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
                    <li>
                        If the inquiry does not result in a commercial
                        relationship, the data will be retained for a maximum of
                        one year from the last contact, unless the user requests
                        its deletion earlier.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        If the inquiry results in a commercial relationship, the
                        data will be retained for the duration of the
                        relationship and, subsequently, for the periods legally
                        required to address potential liabilities (in
                        particular, tax and commercial limitation periods).
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl mb-4">
                    6. Recipients and data processors
                </h2>
                <p>
                    Personal data will not be transferred to third parties,
                    except where legally required. The following service
                    providers act as data processors in the provision of the
                    service:
                </p>
                <ul class="mt-4 list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
                    <li>
                        <strong>Netlify, Inc.</strong> (United States) — website hosting
                        and delivery.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Supabase, Inc.</strong> (United States) — storage
                        of data submitted through the contact form.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Raiola Networks S.L.</strong> (Spain) — hosting of
                        the server that processes the forms via the self-hosted n8n
                        tool.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Google LLC</strong> (United States) — email service
                        (Gmail/Google Workspace) for internal correspondence management.
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <p class="mt-4">
                    Some of these providers are located outside the European
                    Economic Area. International data transfers are carried out
                    with the adequate safeguards required by the GDPR, in
                    particular the Standard Contractual Clauses approved by the
                    European Commission.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl mb-4">7. User rights</h2>
                <p>The user has the right to:</p>
                <ul class="mt-4 list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
                    <li>Access their personal data.</li>
                    <li>
                        Request the rectification of inaccurate or incomplete
                        data.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Request the deletion of their data when it is no longer
                        necessary.
                    </li>
                    <li>Request the restriction of processing.</li>
                    <li>Object to the processing.</li>
                    <li>
                        Request the portability of their data in a structured
                        format.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Withdraw consent at any time, without affecting the
                        lawfulness of processing prior to withdrawal.
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <p class="mt-4">
                    These rights can be exercised by sending an email to <a
                        href="mailto:contacto@jpiedra.com"
                        class="text-accent underline underline-offset-2"
                        >contacto@jpiedra.com</a
                    >, clearly indicating the right being exercised and, if
                    necessary, attaching a document proving the user's identity.
                </p>
                <p class="mt-4">
                    The user also has the right to lodge a complaint with the
                    Spanish Data Protection Agency (AEPD) if they consider that
                    the processing does not comply with current regulations.
                    This can be done at <a
                        href="https://www.aepd.es"
                        target="_blank"
                        rel="noopener noreferrer"
                        class="text-accent underline underline-offset-2"
                        >www.aepd.es</a
                    >.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl mb-4">8. Security measures</h2>
                <p>
                    The data controller applies the technical and organizational
                    measures necessary to ensure the security, integrity, and
                    confidentiality of personal data, preventing its alteration,
                    loss, unauthorized processing, or access.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl mb-4">
                    9. Changes to the privacy policy
                </h2>
                <p>
                    This privacy policy may be updated to reflect legislative
                    changes or modifications to the services provided. The date
                    of the last update is shown at the beginning of the
                    document. Users are advised to review this policy
                    periodically.
                </p>
            </section>
        </div>
    </article>
</Layout>
